While the simulation that is here is outstanding, the fact that you can't freeze chemicals below -100c is -very- disappointing. This leaves out possibilities such as Ln2 and LOx. App would be 5 stars if those features where here.

I like the idea, and I hope it takes off, but it can be inconsistent and glitchy.  For example, putting a beaker on the small ring stand above a bunsen burner to boil water, will result in it explode quickly at around 38 °C.  However, if you instead set the boiling up using the long adjustable ring stand, you can boil the water up to 100.15°C (at which point it won't even try to go higher), no problem what so ever.  Problems like these, and some unresponsive pick up can make the app a little anoying, but I sincerely hope it improves.
